issue.title: The functional API to emulate Attributes is missing Inject features.
Re-evaluate some problematic names to determine alternatives

labels.name: wontfix
labels.description: This will not be worked on

issue.body: Some of the names that were chosen are excessively long or could be improved in some ways. For example, the `ContainerDefinitionCompilerOptionsBuilder` is clunky to work with. Other examples, like `ActiveProfiles` and `ActiveProfilesBuilder` do not match the other conventions used in the library. The `ActiveProfilesBuilder` does not create an instance of `ActiveProfiles`, it builds up an array of string values. Other problems exist in the Defintions where some definitions, or argument names, refer to a service definition, others a type, and still others refer to it as a class. We should do a thorough, holistic look at the Definition interfaces to ensure a cohesive naming strategy is being used.

issue.title: ServiceDefinition and InjectDefinition not implicitly including default profile
issue.body: To ensure that the implied default profile is handled in all the places where a Service or Inject definition might be used those instances should be responsible for ensuring the default profile is included. Currently neither of these implementations are including this value correctly.

issue.title: ContainerFactory instances sharing services without considering active profiles
issue.body: The `AurynContainerFactory` is currently sharing all services found returned from the `ContainerDefinition::getServiceDefinitions`. This is invalid behavior; only services that match the active profiles should be explicitly shared.

issue.title: CacheAwareContainerDefinitionCompiler is dependent on ordering of directories
issue.body: The `CacheAwareContainerDefinitionCompiler` generates a file name in the given cache directory by calling `join()` on the directories that were scanned and passing the resulting string to `md5()`. This implementation would not properly handle if the same directories present in different orders. Tests should be written to ensure that using the cache aware compiler works as expected regardless of the ordering of the scanned directories.

release.name: v0.6.0
release.body:
## What's Changed
* Create CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/96
* Use cspray/annotated-target implementations by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/100
* Bug/type intersect union by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/101
* Ensure nonshared services are not shared by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/103
* Implicitly assign default profile at definition level by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/104
* Add implicit service to get ActiveProfiles by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/105
* Remove ability to not share a service by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/106
* Add ability to autowire a callable by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/107
* Task/0.6 docs by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/115
* Add removal of AnnotatedTarget to changelog by @cspray in https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/pull/116


**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/cspray/annotated-container/compare/v0.5.0...v0.6.0
